<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-31T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="281" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>At their meeting on September 13, the Foreign Ministers of the United
                                States, the United Kingdom and France, discussed the question of
                                access to Berlin and the interzonal trade agreement. For a record of
                                their discussion, see Tripartite Min–5, <ref target="frus1951v03p1#pg_1279">page 1279</ref>.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>